System Architecture
High-Level Agent Flow
This diagram shows how the user interacts with the system and how the Receptionist Agent routes requests to specialized agents.

graph TD
    User((User))
    
    subgraph "Barber Shop Agent System"
        Receptionist[Receptionist Agent<br/>(Router)]
        
        subgraph "Specialized Agents"
            Booking[Booking Agent]
            Consultation[Consultation Agent]
            Followup[Follow-up Agent]
        end
        
        subgraph "Tools & State"
            Calendar[Mock Calendar Tool]
            Vision[Gemini Vision (Mock)]
            State[(Shared Agent State)]
        end
    end

    User <--> Receptionist
    Receptionist -->|Intent: Book| Booking
    Receptionist -->|Intent: Style| Consultation
    Receptionist -->|Intent: Feedback| Followup
    
    Booking <--> Calendar
    Consultation <--> Vision
    
    Booking -->|Done| Receptionist
    Consultation -->|Done| Booking
    Followup -->|Done| Receptionist
    
    Booking -.-> State
    Consultation -.-> State
    Receptionist -.-> State
